The paper deals with algorithms for covering multiple intervals on a line, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves the manipulation of sets and the optimization of movements, which are common topics in data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper mentions applications in mobile sensor barrier coverage in wireless sensor networks, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) and networked systems (cs.NI).
